{
  "texts": [
    "Creates a new graph from the selected nodes by learning a new feature matrix and an adjacency matrix.",
    "These hierarchical pooling methods 21, while employing flat pooling methods (readout) to obtain the graphlevel representation of the coarsened graph, offer various ways to coarsen and process graphs, each with unique advantages in handling graph structure and data reduction.",
    "In this section, we outline the experimental setup, datasets utilized for evaluating the framework, and performance metrics employed.",
    "In our evaluation, we employed well-known propaganda datasets QProp, PTC, and ProText, which have been annotated at the fragment and document levels 2.",
    "QProp is a publicly available annotated corpus offered by the Proppy system 60 at the document-level."
  ]
}